cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.IR 

The paper deals with the problem of semantic labelling, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The paper proposes a method for weakly supervised training, which involves exploiting prior knowledge and image statistics, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also uses a saliency model, which is a common technique in multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) for identifying important regions in an image.
